originalText.text:
There are definitely hints of Nigerianism that go on here but for the most part the process is easy. I have shared a picture of the instructions for passport renewal and also contacts for getting a NIN.
If you come to the embassy and have not printed all the required documents there is a business center that charges close to $10-$15 to print all the required items for you.
You also don‚Äôt need to come on the date of your appointment (you can come earlier or later) but just make sure you have the appointment slip.
Also be sure to have a credit card on you as the final transaction does not allow for cash.
All in on the passport renewal costs around $400 this includes getting a NIN, paying for an appointment online, the USPS overnight shipping, and paying for the passport itself at the location.

There is also a USPS location 7 minutes walk from the location for the USPS overnight self addressed package you are asked to get it cost approximately $30.

As long as you have a NIN you are mostly good to go!

Follow the instructions and the process should be fairly smooth.

This is absolutely intolerable! I completed my biometrics appointment at the consulate on March 23 2023 and my passport was supposed to be ready and delivered in 6weeks according to the consulate officials. However, 9 months passed without communication from the consulate, or any response to my thousands of emails and phone calls to them. On January 3rd 2024, I received a mail, that was supposed to be my passport and I find this letter informing me that my biometric needs to be recaptured (see photo)? Like how? How do you lose a biometric that was captured by your officials, in your consulate?  You‚Äôre a whole organization for Gods sake!!!!!
I have spent time, money and resources to travel 1,200 miles, in March 2023, for this biometric capture and now you tell me that it need to be ‚Äúrecaptured‚Äù, in Jan 2024, with no explanation!  How is this fair please? How?
I don‚Äôt live down the street and the I can‚Äôt just casually stop by.
It‚Äôs cost me so much time and money to come for the initial biometric capture and to tell me all that effort is a waste is just unbelievable.
I refuse to believe this.
I need an explanation from somebody that works here for God‚Äôs sake.

originalText.text:
So, I went to the consulate thinking I was prepared, only to find out that I needed two copies of one of the documents I printed from their website (nothing on their website said you needed two copies) - my advice to folks; take two copies of the three documents you printed out from their website.
By and large, they were mostly nice, except for the younger guy in the screening room. He looked and sounded angry, in my head I was like ‚Äúit is not a crime to make a mistake you know.‚Äù

Updating my review

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
The fundamental issue we have as a country is lack of empathy. I thought when my call was answered that I would have a solution to my problem but it became worse! These guys don‚Äôt care and it baffles me bitterly. The worst part of this is that they are benefiting from tax payers money and service charges, what am I truly benefiting from the consulate rather than pain and suffering!

Nigeria needs to be recolonized and everyone relearn a new culture cos we will never get it right! It‚Äôs so painful that you have a trip to make and you can‚Äôt even get your passport expedited through the right channel.

There has to be a way to get this right! But, no one cares!

FIRST REVIEW!
I never thought I would be giving a 5 Start review. But hear me out. For the first time, a lady picked up the phone, she was so cautious, calm and assertive. I was shocked! I was like, am I I dreaming.

After I laid down my complaints, I was assured that I would get a response with regards to my complaints.

Guess what‚Ä¶

The next day, I got a call from the same lady and I was like üò≥ is this for real. She assured me that I should get an update soon.

But I wish they tighten this relationship across board. It‚Äôs not that hard, you just have to be firm with your policies, structure, hire the right people and always work hard for the people cos we the tax payers are the ones who keep your job going - it‚Äôs a win win for us all.
